body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting CarZone Support. My name is Logan Wood and I'm with CarZone. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Jacqueline. Could you please provide me with your phone number so we can assist you better?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my phone number is five five five two three four one zero.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Jacqueline. And can you also verify your mailing address for us?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my mailing address is one two three Main Street, Cityville, ABC 1 2 3.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for the information, Jacqueline. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all. Thank you for your help.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Jacqueline. If you have any more questions in the future, feel free to reach out. Have a great day!
